  "prompt": "Is it forbidden in Islam to name your child Allah?",
  "response": "In Islam, it is generally considered inappropriate to name a child \"Allah.\" The name \"Allah\" is the Arabic word for God and holds a significant and sacred status in Islam. Names that are attributes or names of God are usually discouraged for human beings because they can imply a level of divinity that belongs solely to God.\n\nIslamic scholars recommend that parents choose names that have good meanings and are respectful. Names of prophets, righteous figures, or names that reflect positive attributes are often preferred. It's always a good idea for parents to consult with knowledgeable individuals or religious authorities for guidance on naming children in accordance with Islamic teachings.",
